To ensure the integrity of the training labels, a Python-based automated cleaning utility was implemented. This script parses the `.csv` annotation files to remove 
    \item Label Normalization: Removes the artifact suffix "\_proposals" from the name column to standardize class labels.（generated during previous model predictions.）
    \item Invalid Entry Pruning: Filters out rows where the fourth column contains a value of -1, indicating an invalid annotation index.
    \item Noise Removal: Eliminates rows explicitly labeled as "noise".
