\subsection{Syllable Segmentation}
为了用于后面对不同音符的分析, an automated segmentation routine was developed in MATLAB. This method leverages the accurate time-based annotations previously created for the song sequences.
he automated segmentation process directly utilizes the time-based labels exported from the manual annotation phase (e.g., CSV format). This approach ensures that the output segments precisely match the boundaries defined during human review.

\begin{itemize} \item \textbf{Input Data:} The process requires two inputs: the original WAV audio file and the corresponding annotation file (CSV/Excel) containing the start and end times for each syllable. 
\item \textbf{Segmentation Logic:} The custom MATLAB script loads the annotation file to retrieve the specific \texttt{Start Time (s)} and \texttt{End Time (s)} for every entry.
\item \textbf{Output Generation:} The script iterates through each annotated syllable, extracts the corresponding audio data array using matrix slicing, and then exports the clipped segment as a separate WAV file using the \texttt{audiowrite} function.
\item \textbf{Result:} This batch processing capability allows for the rapid generation of a large dataset of individually labeled syllable audio files, which is essential for the subsequent feature extraction and DAS model training. 
\end{itemize}
