7.1 跨模型预测能力
the model's predictive accuracy on its primary training channel (CH3) reached a stable state. However, significant performance degradation was observed when applying the model to cross-channel data (CH0), highlighting a critical need for enhanced model generalization.
7.2
The primary challenge is the "domain shift" observed between recording channels. Small variations in background noise and signal-to-noise ratios between CH3 and CH0 cause the model to fail on pulse-like syllables.
    \item \textbf{Environmental Noise Sensitivity}: 
    Background noise remains a primary factor constraining generalization. In environments with a low signal-to-noise ratio (SNR), the model is prone to misclassification, as it struggles to distinguish faint syllable features from ambient interference. 

    \item \textbf{High Variability in Non-Breeding Season Data}: 
    The dataset collected in November 2023 (non-breeding season) presents a unique challenge due to significant \textit{acoustic plasticity}. Unlike the stereotypical songs produced during the breeding season, vocalizations from this period exhibit unstable morphology and inconsistent spectral features. 
    Crucially, \textbf{continuous syllable sequences are almost non-existent} in this dataset. This lack of sequential context deprives human annotators of the ability to identify syllable types through comparative analysis, making manual annotation prohibitively difficult and subjective.

    \subsection{Future Optimization Strategies}
To address the aforementioned challenges, we propose the following directions for optimization:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Context-Aware Post-Processing}: 
    To mitigate noise-induced errors, I plan to leverage the syllable statistics and N-gram patterns derived from analysis result. A \textbf{logic-based filter} to correct sporadic errors can be implemented. For instance, in a stable repetitive sequence (e.g., $A \to A \to \dots$), if noise causes a sudden glitch (e.g., $A \to B \to A$), this anomaly can be detected and corrected by verifying transition probabilities and temporal consistency.

    \item \textbf{Refinement of Class Definitions}: 
    Future work will involve revisiting the outliers identified in the duration analysis. The syllable class definitions need to be refined to ensure distinct and robust boundaries. By cleaning the training data of ambiguous labels, the model's ability to generalize can be improved, even on more variable data.
